<TITLE> Hospital soon to treat FFs: Tajul </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 25 (bdnews24.com)--A hospital will be built in Dhaka to treat freedom fighters (FFs) free of cost, the state minister for liberation war said on Friday. The hospital at a cost of Tk 75 crore will be built at Tejgaon in Dhaka, ABM Tajul Islam said, speaking at a reunion ceremony of freedom fighters in the city. The elderly freedom fighters who fought under Sector 7 during 1971 independence war met at the ceremony at Agargaon. Many of them spoke at the ceremony about inconsistencies in the current freedom fighters' list. Islam said in many cases, enrolled freedom fighters helped those who did not fight the war to enrol as freedom fighters. The government has begun work but it needs time to purge the list of fake names, he added. b
